XmAddressBook - A Motif Address Book - Version 1.5.3

Copyright 1994,1995,1996 by Boyd Fletcher and Old Dominion University

Send problems/questions to: boyd@ccpo.odu.edu

NOTE: This used to be called XmRolodex.


DESCRIPTION:

XmAddressbook is a X11/Motif based Address Book program. It can convert the old
rolo program's rolodex.dat files into its own format. 

SUPPORTED SYSTEMS:

Company			Machine			OS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sun Microsystems	SPARCstations		Solaris 1.x (SUNOS 4.1.x)
						using GCC
Sun Microsystems	SPARCstations		Solaris 2.x (SUNOS 5.x) 
IBM			RS/6000 		AIX 3.2.x and AIX 4.1
Silicon Graphics	Indigo 2		IRIX 5.x
DEC 			AXP 3000/600		OSF 2.0b
Solbourne		Series 5/600            OS/MP 4.1C using GCC
Hewlett Packard		HP 9000/735             HP-UX 9.X
Novell			Intel x86, Pentium	UnixWare 1.1 & UnixWare 2.0
BSDI			Intel x86, Pentium	BSDI 1.1
OpenVMS			Alpha & VAX		OpenVMS 6.1 and 6.2 (X11R5/Motif 1.2)

NOTE: I have tested XmAddressBook on the following SunOS, AIX, IRIX,
and OS/MP.

INSTALLATION: (except OpenVMS)

1) Edit Imakefile if you are using X11R6

2) If you have Imake, then type: xmkmf

3) type: make

4) type: make install

5) type: make install.man

OR,

1) type: cp Makefile.noimake Makefile

2) Edit the Makefile for your specific machine. Paying particular
attention to the following fields:

HELP_FILE=/usr/local/X11/lib/X11/xmaddressbook/xmaddressbook.hlp
BIN_DIR=/usr/local/X11/bin
MAN_DIR=/usr/local/X11/man/man1
APP_DEFAULTS_DIR=/usr/local/X11/lib/X11/app-defaults
APP_DEFAULTS=XmAddressbook
MAN_PAGE=xmaddressbook.1

3) type: make 

4) type: make install


OpenVMS:

Take a look at the DESCRIP.MMS (similar to Unix's imake program) and
MAKE.COM files. (thanks to Martin P.J. Zinser, m.zinser@gsi.de)

PORTING:

If you port it to another platform please send be the diffs and the
options used to compile it.

HOW TO GET IT:

Using anonymous ftp:

ftp ftp.ccpo.odu.edu

Connected to ftp.ccpo.odu.edu.
220 kuroshio FTP server (SunOS 4.1) ready.
Name (ftp.ccpo.odu.edu:boyd): ftp
331 Guest login ok, send ident as password.
Password:  (use your login name here)
230 Guest login ok, access restrictions apply.
ftp> cd pub/boyd
250 CWD command successful.
ftp> bin
200 Type set to I.
ftp> get xmaddressbook-Maj.Min.Rev.tar.Z

